rComments: Such a good guy, such a good teacher. I had him for critical thinking his first semester teaching and we were so surprised when he told us. Great for help outside of class.

The biggest sweetheart on planet, and made something as dry of a subject as critical thinking actually enjoyable. He understands that critical thinking is not something that comes naturally to everyone, and makes a wonderful effort in creating analogies that help relate life experience to the class material. Very kind and incredibly intelligent!

Amazing professor, young but motivated and passionate.  Really cares that student really learn and understand critical reasoning.  Gives good examples, good feedback.  He's not afraid of admitting when he's wrong, which gives him lot's of credit as a teacher.  Likes interacting with students.  YOU MUST SHOW UP IN CLASS IN ORDER TO BENEFIT!!!

He is an amazing prof, one of my favourites. He is always there to help his students and clearly explains expectations for the class. He made philosophy- which can be difficult at times,  a lot easier to understand. And her genuinely cares about how his students are doing in class.

He is a very good prof, one of my best profs in Uottawa. His office hours are really helpful because the course takes a lot of critical reasoning, it's not as easy as people think it  is, takes a lot of practices. But he is very straightforward in tests.  Take his class.
Gives great reviews regarding the exams, makes lectures somewhat interesting in a really dry subject, don't need to go to class though as he posts what readings and excercises to do
Although he is new, he is a good prof.
